text: Dubki () is a rural locality (a village) in Bulgakovsky Selsoviet, Ufimsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 219 as of 2010. There are 9 streets. == Geography == It is located 32 km from Ufa, 2 km from Bulgakovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Ufimsky District
title: Dubki, Republic of Bashkortostan
